Amazon’s first contactless store outside of the United States opened in Ealing, London.New software in CCTV cameras can now match footage of motorists throwing rubbish to their car’s number plate and issue an immediate fine of £90.  A “LitterCam” that is watching you, a shape-changing smartphone, electronic scooters, all-electric cars and a store where you can pick up your food and walk straight out... this is the future which is becoming our present.  

It is an exciting new world for many in Britain, especially younger people, but others are not so sure, including civil liberties campaigners.  



